### ðŸ§® Step 1: Determine the Ring Containing 2026

The total number of natural numbers up to ring $ n $ is given by:

$$
T(n) = 1 + 3n(n+1)
$$

We want to find the smallest $ n $ such that $ T(n) \geq 2026 $.

Trying $ n = 26 $:

$$
T(25) = 1 + 3 \cdot 25 \cdot 26 = 1 + 1950 = 1951 \\
T(26) = 1 + 3 \cdot 26 \cdot 27 = 1 + 2106 = 2107
$$

So, **2026 lies in ring 26**, as $ T(25) < 2026 \leq T(26) $.

Its position **within ring 26** is:
$$
\text{pos\_in\_ring} = 2026 - 1951 = 75
$$

---

### ðŸ§© Step 2: Identify Side and Offset Within the Side

Each ring has 6 sides, each of length $ n $ (in this case, 26). Divide 75 into regions of 26 to find which side it is on:

$$
75 \div 26 = 2\ \text{remainder}\ 23 \Rightarrow \text{side 2 (0-indexed)},\ \text{offset} = 23
$$

